<item>
            <title>[LU-14767] mkfs.lustre unable to disable lazy_itable_init=0</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14767</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/38534&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/38534&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13533&quot; title=&quot;Disable lazy_itable_init&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13533&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13533&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; utils: ext4lazyinit should be disabled&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; added &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lazy_itable_init=0&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to the mke2fs options.  However, the check to see whether &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lazy_itable_init&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; is already listed in the options is broken.  It looks if &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lazy_itable_init=0&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; is already present and doesn&apos;t match &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lazy_itable_init=1&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; if it was specified on the command-line.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
